License Grant (Execution)

Upon payment and acknowledgment, the licensee is granted:

A non-exclusive execution license

Permission to build, test, propose, and commercialize

Rights limited to GEMS-derived work

No exclusivity is implied unless separately negotiated.

License Restrictions

Without a Phase 3 execution license, you may not:

Build

Test

Fabricate

Propose

Manufacture

Sell

Deploy

Any such activity without authorization constitutes a license violation.

Termination

License terminates immediately upon breach

No retroactive permission is granted

All execution rights cease upon termination

Relationship to Earlier Phases

Phase 1 and Phase 2 remain frozen and unchanged

Phase 3 does not retroactively modify earlier phases

Phase 3 may contradict earlier assumptions during execution

Earlier phases inform execution but do not constrain it.

Plain-English Summary

Phase 3 is the point where thinking turns into permission. Paying the $5,000 execution fee grants the right to build, test, propose, or commercialize GEMS-derived work. Nothing before Phase 3 authorizes execution.
